cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.LO, cs.SY, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with controller synthesis for multi-agent systems.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the dynamics of agents and their control inputs.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses Metric Interval Temporal Logic (MITL) for high-level specification.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with controller synthesis and dynamics of multi-agent systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes an algorithm for computing individual runs that satisfy high-level tasks.
